BEGIN_PGML
In this challenge, your job is to create expressions, using addition, subtraction, multiplication, and parentheses. You may use the numbers, [`1, 2, 3\text{,}`] and [`4`] in your expression, using each number only once. For example, you could make the expression: [`1+2 \cdot 3 - 4\text{.}`]

a.  The greatest value that it is possible to create under these conditions is [_]{36}{10}.

a.  The least value that it is possible to create under these conditions is [_]{-23}{10}.

END_PGML

############################################################
# Solution
############################################################

BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION
a.  The greatest value is [`36\text{,}`] which comes from [`(1+2) \cdot 3 \cdot 4\text{.}`]

a.  The least value is [`-23\text{,}`] which comes from [`1 - (2 \cdot 3 \cdot 4)\text{.}`]

END_PGML_SOLUTION

